The paper proposes a new graph generative model that focuses on matching the properties of real graphs and the natural variance expected for the corresponding population. This falls under the category of statistical inference (SI) and machine learning (LG). The paper also discusses the ability of the proposed model to scale to massive graph sizes, which suggests a focus on data management (DM) and system development (SD). Finally, the paper mentions the experimental evaluation of the proposed model on publicly available graph datasets, which suggests a focus on network science (NE).
